---
const templates = [
  {
    category: 'launch',
    name: 'Launch reveal',
    when: 'For announcing a product, feature, or update with clarity.',
    structure: 'Hook with the promised outcome -> why it matters now -> what changed -> who it is for -> CTA.',
    example: 'After weeks of patchwork workflows, I built a simpler X drafting system for solo creators. Here is what it fixes and who it helps.',
  },
  {
    category: 'authority',
    name: 'Lesson thread',
    when: 'For turning a hard-earned insight into authority content.',
    structure: 'Bold claim -> context -> 3 practical lessons -> common mistake -> takeaway.',
    example: 'Most creators do not need more ideas. They need a cleaner publishing system. Three lessons changed that for me.',
  },
  {
    category: 'authority',
    name: 'Case-study breakdown',
    when: 'For sharing a result and making it teachable.',
    structure: 'Result -> starting point -> what changed -> 3 tactical moves -> what to copy.',
    example: 'A small workflow change doubled the number of posts I could ship each week. Here is the breakdown.',
  },
  {
    category: 'story',
    name: 'Founder story',
    when: 'For relationship-building posts with a personal angle.',
    structure: 'Scene -> tension -> decision -> lesson -> next chapter.',
    example: 'I kept blaming the algorithm until I realized the real problem was my content system.',
  },
  {
    category: 'engagement',
    name: 'Contrarian take',
    when: 'For strong opinions that invite replies without sounding combative.',
    structure: 'Common advice -> where it fails -> your alternative -> one example -> question back to readers.',
    example: 'Hot take: most creators should stop chasing automation and fix their drafts first.',
  },
  {
    category: 'engagement',
    name: 'Question-led post',
    when: 'For collecting replies while signaling expertise.',
    structure: 'Specific question -> 2 constraints -> why you are asking -> invite examples.',
    example: 'What is one X workflow you would pay for, and what part would you still want to keep manual?',
  },
  {
    category: 'education',
    name: 'Mini framework',
    when: 'For teaching a repeatable process in a compact way.',
    structure: 'Name the framework -> 3 steps -> when to use it -> mistake to avoid.',
    example: 'My 3-part thread formula: hook, proof, pull. Use it when your post has one core lesson.',
  },
  {
    category: 'education',
    name: 'Mistake / fix',
    when: 'For content that starts with a painful error and resolves it fast.',
    structure: 'Mistake -> why it hurts -> fix -> small example -> action step.',
    example: 'Mistake: turning every thread into a life story. Fix: lead with the reader payoff before your context.',
  },
  {
    category: 'launch',
    name: 'Feature spotlight',
    when: 'For introducing a single feature without writing a full launch thread.',
    structure: 'Problem -> feature -> what changes -> who should use it -> CTA.',
    example: 'Creators told me templates were easy to save but hard to reuse. So I built a local library that keeps the structure ready to copy.',
  },
];
---

<section id="workbench" class="w-full max-w-7xl mx-auto space-y-6" data-workbench>
  <div class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-200/80 bg-white shadow-sm overflow-hidden flex flex-col">
    <div class="border-b border-zinc-100 bg-zinc-50/50 p-4 sm:p-5 flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center justify-between gap-4">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900">X Growth Workbench</h2>
        <p class="mt-1 text-[13px] text-zinc-500">Draft threads, browse templates, and generate value-add replies.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="flex p-1 rounded-lg bg-zinc-100/80 ring-1 ring-zinc-900/5" role="tablist" aria-label="XHunter tools">
        <button class="tab-button active flex-1 sm:flex-none" type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="true" data-tab="thread">Thread Maker</button>
        <button class="tab-button flex-1 sm:flex-none" type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="templates">Templates</button>
        <button class="tab-button flex-1 sm:flex-none" type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="reply">Reply</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="p-5 sm:p-6 lg:p-8 bg-zinc-50/30">
      <section class="tab-panel active" data-panel="thread" role="tabpanel" aria-label="Thread Maker">
        <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[1.1fr_0.9fr] lg:items-start">
          <div class="flex flex-col rounded-2xl border border-zinc-200/80 bg-white shadow-sm p-5 sm:p-6">
            <div class="mb-5 pb-5 border-b border-zinc-100">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                <span class="flex h-5 w-5 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-zinc-100 text-[11px] font-semibold text-zinc-500">01</span>
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900">Turn an idea into a thread</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-[13px] text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed">
                Paste a blog excerpt, notes, or a rough idea. Reshape it into a structured thread draft.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div>
                <label class="block text-[13px] font-medium text-zinc-700 mb-1.5">Source text</label>
                <textarea id="thread-source" class="w-full h-40 rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-50 p-3.5 text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-zinc-900 placeholder:text-zinc-400 focus:border-zinc-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-4 focus:ring-zinc-900/5 transition-all resize-y" placeholder="Paste a blog paragraph, notes, or a rough creator insight."></textarea>
              </div>
              
              <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
                <div class="sm:col-span-2">
                  <label class="block text-[13px] font-medium text-zinc-700 mb-1.5">Goal <span class="text-zinc-400 font-normal ml-1">Optional</span></label>
                  <input id="thread-goal" class="w-full rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-white px-3 py-2 text-[13px] text-zinc-900 placeholder:text-zinc-400 focus:border-zinc-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-4 focus:ring-zinc-900/5 transition-all" type="text" placeholder="Example: get more saves from creator-operators" />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <label class="block text-[13px] font-medium text-zinc-700 mb-1.5">Tone</label>
                  <select id="thread-tone" class="w-full rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-white px-3 py-2 text-[13px] text-zinc-900 focus:border-zinc-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-4 focus:ring-zinc-900/5 transition-all">
                    <option value="sharp">Sharp</option>
                    <option value="analytical">Analytical</option>
                    <option value="warm">Warm</option>
                    <option value="contrarian">Contrarian</option>
                  </select>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <label class="block text-[13px] font-medium text-zinc-700 mb-1.5">Posts count</label>
                  <select id="thread-count" class="w-full rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-white px-3 py-2 text-[13px] text-zinc-900 focus:border-zinc-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-4 focus:ring-zinc-900/5 transition-all">
                    <option value="6">6 posts</option>
                    <option value="7" selected>7 posts</option>
                    <option value="8">8 posts</option>
                    <option value="9">9 posts</option>
                  </select>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="pt-2">
                <button id="thread-generate" class="w-full sm:w-auto btn btn--primary" type="button">Build thread draft</button>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex flex-col h-full min-h-[500px] rounded-2xl border border-zinc-200/80 bg-zinc-50 shadow-sm overflow-hidden">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between border-b border-zinc-200/80 bg-white p-4">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900">Output Draft</h3>
              <button id="thread-copy" class="text-[13px] font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-700 transition-colors hidden flex items-center gap-1" type="button">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w0.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" class="size-3.5">
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M15.988 3.012A2.25 2.25 0 0 1 18 5.25v6.5A2.25 2.25 0 0 1 15.75 14H13.5V7A2.5 2.5 0 0 0 11 4.5H8.128a2.252 2.252 0 0 1 1.884-1.488A2.25 2.25 0 0 1 12.25 1h1.5a2.25 2.25 0 0 1 2.238 2.012ZM11.5 3.25a.75.75 0 0 1 .75-.75h1.5a.75.75 0 0 1 .75.75v.25h-3v-.25Z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                  <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M2 7a1 1 0 0 1 1-1h8a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v10a1 1 0 0 1-1 1H3a1 1 0 0 1-1-1V7Zm2 3.25a.75.75 0 0 1 .75-.75h4.5a.75.75 0 0 1 0 1.5h-4.5a.75.75 0 0 1-.75-.75Zm0 3.5a.75.75 0 0 1 .75-.75h4.5a.75.75 0 0 1 0 1.5h-4.5a.75.75 0 0 1-.75-.75Z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                </svg>
                Copy all
              </button>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1 p-4 sm:p-5 overflow-y-auto">
              <ol id="thread-results" class="space-y-4">
                <li class="flex items-center justify-center h-full min-h-[300px]">
                  <p id="thread-status" class="text-[13px] text-zinc-500 text-center" aria-live="polite">Configure your settings and build to see the thread here.</p>
                </li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="tab-panel hidden" data-panel="templates" role="tabpanel" aria-label="Template Library">
        <div class="flex flex-col space-y-6">
          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2" role="toolbar" aria-label="Template filters">
            <button class="filter-button active" type="button" data-filter="all">All Templates</button>
            <button class="filter-button" type="button" data-filter="launch">Launch</button>
            <button class="filter-button" type="button" data-filter="authority">Authority</button>
            <button class="filter-button" type="button" data-filter="story">Story</button>
            <button class="filter-button" type="button" data-filter="engagement">Engagement</button>
            <button class="filter-button" type="button" data-filter="education">Education</button>
          </div>

          <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
            {templates.map((template) => (
              <article class="template-card flex flex-col rounded-2xl border border-zinc-200/80 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm transition-all duration-300 hover:border-zinc-300 hover:shadow-md" data-category={template.category}>
                <div class="mb-3">
                  <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-zinc-100 px-2 py-0.5 text-[11px] font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-zinc-600 ring-1 ring-inset ring-zinc-500/10">
                    {template.category}
                  </span>
                </div>
                <h4 class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-2">{template.name}</h4>
                <div class="space-y-3 flex-1 mb-5">
                  <p class="text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-zinc-600"><strong class="text-zinc-900 font-medium">Use when:</strong> {template.when}</p>
                  <p class="text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-zinc-600"><strong class="text-zinc-900 font-medium">Structure:</strong> {template.structure}</p>
                  <div class="rounded-lg bg-zinc-50 p-3 border border-zinc-100">
                    <p class="text-[12px] leading-relaxed text-zinc-500 italic">"{template.example}"</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <button
                  class="btn btn--secondary w-full copy-template group"
                  type="button"
                  data-copy={`${template.name}\n\nUse it when: ${template.when}\nStructure: ${template.structure}\nExample: ${template.example}`}
                >
                  <span>Copy Template</span>
                  <svg xmlns="http://www.w0.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor" class="size-3.5 opacity-50 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M15.988 3.012A2.25 2.25 0 0 1 18 5.25v6.5A2.25 2.25 0 0 1 15.75 14H13.5V7A2.5 2.5 0 0 0 11 4.5H8.128a2.252 2.252 0 0 1 1.884-1.488A2.25 2.25 0 0 1 12.25 1h1.5a2.25 2.25 0 0 1 2.238 2.012ZM11.5 3.25a.75.75 0 0 1 .75-.75h1.5a.75.75 0 0 1 .75.75v.25h-3v-.25Z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M2 7a1 1 0 0 1 1-1h8a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v10a1 1 0 0 1-1 1H3a1 1 0 0 1-1-1V7Zm2 3.25a.75.75 0 0 1 .75-.75h4.5a.75.75 0 0 1 0 1.5h-4.5a.75.75 0 0 1-.75-.75Zm0 3.5a.75.75 0 0 1 .75-.75h4.5a.75.75 0 0 1 0 1.5h-4.5a.75.75 0 0 1-.75-.75Z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
                  </svg>
                </button>
              </article>
            ))}
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-center">
            <p class="rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-emerald-600 ring-1 ring-inset ring-emerald-500/20 opacity-0 transition-opacity" id="template-status" aria-live="polite">Template copied to clipboard</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="tab-panel hidden" data-panel="reply" role="tabpanel" aria-label="Reply Assistant">
        <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_1fr] lg:items-start">
          <div class="flex flex-col rounded-2xl border border-zinc-200/80 bg-white shadow-sm p-5 sm:p-6">
            <div class="mb-5 pb-5 border-b border-zinc-100">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                <span class="flex h-5 w-5 items-center justify-center rounded-md bg-zinc-100 text-[11px] font-semibold text-zinc-500">03</span>
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900">Draft stronger replies</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-[13px] text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed">
                Paste a post. XHunter suggests multiple value-add reply angles.
              </p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div>
                <label class="block text-[13px] font-medium text-zinc-700 mb-1.5">Target post</label>
                <textarea id="reply-source" class="w-full h-32 rounded-xl border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-50 p-3.5 text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-zinc-900 placeholder:text-zinc-400 focus:border-zinc-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-4 focus:ring-zinc-900/5 transition-all resize-y" placeholder="Paste the post or the main point you want to reply to."></textarea>
              </div>
              
              <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
                <div>
                  <label class="block text-[13px] font-medium text-zinc-700 mb-1.5">Your angle</label>
                  <input id="reply-angle" class="w-full rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-white px-3 py-2 text-[13px] text-zinc-900 placeholder:text-zinc-400 focus:border-zinc-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-4 focus:ring-zinc-900/5 transition-all" type="text" placeholder="e.g. solo creator workflows" />
                </div>
                <div>
                  <label class="block text-[13px] font-medium text-zinc-700 mb-1.5">Style</label>
                  <select id="reply-style" class="w-full rounded-lg border border-zinc-200 bg-white px-3 py-2 text-[13px] text-zinc-900 focus:border-zinc-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-4 focus:ring-zinc-900/5 transition-all">
                    <option value="add_value">Add value</option>
                    <option value="question">Ask a smart question</option>
                    <option value="agreement">Agree and extend</option>
                    <option value="contrarian">Respectful pushback</option>
                  </select>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="pt-2">
                <button id="reply-generate" class="w-full sm:w-auto btn btn--primary" type="button">Draft replies</button>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex flex-col h-full min-h-[400px] rounded-2xl border border-zinc-200/80 bg-zinc-50 shadow-sm overflow-hidden">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between border-b border-zinc-200/80 bg-white p-4">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900">Reply Angles</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1 p-4 sm:p-5 overflow-y-auto">
              <div id="reply-results" class="space-y-4">
                <div class="flex items-center justify-center h-full min-h-[200px]">
                  <p id="reply-status" class="text-[13px] text-zinc-500 text-center" aria-live="polite">Your generated reply options will appear here.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  @reference "../styles/global.css";

  .tab-button {
    @apply px-4 py-2 text-[13px] font-medium text-zinc-500 rounded-md transition-all duration-200;
  }
  .tab-button:hover {
    @apply text-zinc-900;
  }
  .tab-button.active {
    @apply bg-white text-zinc-900 shadow-sm ring-1 ring-zinc-900/5;
  }
  
  .filter-button {
    @apply px-3 py-1.5 text-xs font-medium rounded-full border border-zinc-200 bg-white text-zinc-600 transition-colors hover:bg-zinc-50 hover:text-zinc-900;
  }
  .filter-button.active {
    @apply border-transparent bg-zinc-900 text-white;
  }

  .output-item {
    @apply rounded-xl border border-zinc-200/80 bg-white p-4 shadow-sm;
  }
</style>

<script>
  (() => {
    const root = document.querySelector<HTMLElement>('[data-workbench]');
    if (!root) return;

    type ThreadTone = 'sharp' | 'analytical' | 'warm' | 'contrarian';
    type ReplyStyle = 'add_value' | 'question' | 'agreement' | 'contrarian';

    const query = <T extends Element>(selector: string) => root.querySelector<T>(selector);
    const queryAll = <T extends Element>(selector: string) => Array.from(root.querySelectorAll<T>(selector));

    const tabs = queryAll<HTMLButtonElement>('[data-tab]');
    const panels = queryAll<HTMLElement>('[data-panel]');

    const setTab = (name: string) => {
      tabs.forEach((tab) => {
        const active = tab.dataset.tab === name;
        tab.classList.toggle('active', active);
        tab.setAttribute('aria-selected', active ? 'true' : 'false');
      });

      panels.forEach((panel) => {
        if (panel.dataset.panel === name) {
          panel.classList.remove('hidden');
        } else {
          panel.classList.add('hidden');
        }
      });
    };

    tabs.forEach((tab) => {
      tab.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const tabName = tab.dataset.tab;
        if (tabName) setTab(tabName);
      });
    });

    const safeText = (value: string) => value.replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim();

    const clip = async (text: string, statusNode: HTMLElement | null, successMessage: string) => {
      if (!text) {
        if (statusNode) statusNode.textContent = 'Nothing to copy yet.';
        return;
      }

      try {
        await navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
        if (statusNode) {
          statusNode.textContent = successMessage;
          statusNode.classList.remove('opacity-0');
          setTimeout(() => statusNode.classList.add('opacity-0'), 2000);
        }
      } catch {
        if (statusNode) statusNode.textContent = 'Copy failed. Select the text manually.';
      }
    };

    const fitPost = (prefix: string, body: string) => {
      const limit = 278 - prefix.length;
      const clean = safeText(body);
      if (clean.length <= limit) return clean;

      const trimmed = clean.slice(0, Math.max(0, limit - 1));
      const cut = trimmed.lastIndexOf(' ');
      return `${(cut > 80 ? trimmed.slice(0, cut) : trimmed).trim()}…`;
    };

    const splitSource = (text: string): string[] =>
      text
        .split(/\n+/)
        .flatMap((line: string) => line.split(/(?<=[.!?。！？])\s+/))
        .map((line: string) => safeText(line.replace(/^[-*]\s*/, '')))
        .filter(Boolean);

    const summarizeTopic = (text: string) => {
      const clean = safeText(text);
      if (!clean) return 'your idea';
      const compact = clean.replace(/[.?!。！？].*$/, '');
      return compact.slice(0, 72).trim();
    };

    const threadSource = query<HTMLTextAreaElement>('#thread-source');
    const threadGoal = query<HTMLInputElement>('#thread-goal');
    const threadTone = query<HTMLSelectElement>('#thread-tone');
    const threadCount = query<HTMLSelectElement>('#thread-count');
    const threadGenerate = query<HTMLButtonElement>('#thread-generate');
    const threadCopy = query<HTMLButtonElement>('#thread-copy');
    const threadStatus = query<HTMLElement>('#thread-status');
    const threadResults = query<HTMLOListElement>('#thread-results');

    if (!threadSource || !threadGoal || !threadTone || !threadCount || !threadGenerate || !threadCopy || !threadStatus || !threadResults) {
      return;
    }

    let lastThread = '';

    const renderThread = (posts: string[]) => {
      threadResults.innerHTML = '';
      threadCopy.classList.remove('hidden');

      posts.forEach((post: string, index: number) => {
        const li = document.createElement('li');
        li.className = 'output-item';

        const head = document.createElement('div');
        head.className = 'flex items-center justify-between mb-2 pb-2 border-b border-zinc-100';

        const label = document.createElement('strong');
        label.className = 'text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-zinc-400';
        label.textContent = `Post ${index + 1}`;

        const chars = document.createElement('span');
        chars.className = 'text-[11px] font-medium text-zinc-400 bg-zinc-50 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded';
        chars.textContent = `${post.length} chars`;

        head.append(label, chars);

        const body = document.createElement('p');
        body.className = 'text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-zinc-900 whitespace-pre-wrap';
        body.textContent = post;

        li.append(head, body);
        threadResults.append(li);
      });
    };

    const buildThread = () => {
      const source = threadSource.value.trim();
      const goal = threadGoal.value.trim();
      const count = Number(threadCount.value) || 7;

      if (!source) {
        threadSource.focus();
        return;
      }

      const chunks = splitSource(source);
      const topic = summarizeTopic(goal || chunks[0] || source);

      const hooks: Record<ThreadTone, string> = {
        sharp: `If you want better X posts without more busywork, use this ${count}-post draft on ${topic}.`,
        analytical: `Here is a ${count}-post X thread structure you can use to turn ${topic} into a clearer argument.`,
        warm: `If ${topic} matters to your audience, here is a simple ${count}-post thread you can build from it.`,
        contrarian: `Most creators overcomplicate threads. Here is the cleaner ${count}-post version for ${topic}.`,
      };

      const toneLine: Record<ThreadTone, string> = {
        sharp: 'Lead with the payoff before your context.',
        analytical: 'Break the idea into one promise, a few proof points, and one clear takeaway.',
        warm: 'Keep the thread useful and conversational, not performative.',
        contrarian: 'Challenge the default advice, then explain what works better.',
      };

      const tone = (threadTone.value in hooks ? threadTone.value : 'sharp') as ThreadTone;

      const posts: string[] = [
        hooks[tone],
        `Core angle: ${goal || `help creators understand ${topic}`}. ${toneLine[tone]}`,
      ];

      const sourceBullets = chunks.slice(0, Math.max(2, count - 3));

      sourceBullets.forEach((chunk: string, index: number) => {
        const cleaned = safeText(chunk);
        if (!cleaned) return;

        const prefaces = [
          'Start here:',
          'Then make this concrete:',
          'Add proof:',
          'Give one example:',
          'Name the mistake:',
          'Close the gap:',
        ];

        posts.push(`${prefaces[index] || 'Keep it specific:'} ${cleaned}`);
      });

      while (posts.length < count - 1) {
        posts.push(`Keep each post focused on one move. If a sentence does not earn the scroll, cut it.`);
      }

      posts.push(`If this is useful, rewrite your next X thread with one hook, three proof points, and one direct CTA.`);

      const numberedPosts = posts.slice(0, count).map((post, index, list) => {
        const prefix = `${index + 1}/${list.length} `;
        return `${prefix}${fitPost(prefix, post)}`;
      });

      lastThread = numberedPosts.join('\n\n');
      renderThread(numberedPosts);
    };

    threadGenerate.addEventListener('click', buildThread);
    threadCopy.addEventListener('click', () => clip(lastThread, null, ''));

    const filterButtons = queryAll<HTMLButtonElement>('[data-filter]');
    const templateCards = queryAll<HTMLElement>('.template-card');
    const templateStatus = query<HTMLElement>('#template-status');

    filterButtons.forEach((button) => {
      button.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const filter = button.dataset.filter ?? 'all';

        filterButtons.forEach((item) => item.classList.toggle('active', item === button));
        templateCards.forEach((card) => {
          const visible = filter === 'all' || card.dataset.category === filter;
          card.classList.toggle('hidden', !visible);
          card.classList.toggle('flex', visible);
        });
      });
    });

    queryAll<HTMLButtonElement>('.copy-template').forEach((button) => {
      button.addEventListener('click', async () => {
        const originalText = button.innerHTML;
        await clip(button.dataset.copy || '', templateStatus, 'Template copied!');
        button.innerHTML = '<span class="text-emerald-600">Copied!</span>';
        setTimeout(() => { button.innerHTML = originalText; }, 1500);
      });
    });

    const replySource = query<HTMLTextAreaElement>('#reply-source');
    const replyAngle = query<HTMLInputElement>('#reply-angle');
    const replyStyle = query<HTMLSelectElement>('#reply-style');
    const replyGenerate = query<HTMLButtonElement>('#reply-generate');
    const replyResults = query<HTMLElement>('#reply-results');

    if (!replySource || !replyAngle || !replyStyle || !replyGenerate || !replyResults) {
      return;
    }

    const renderReplies = (items: string[]) => {
      replyResults.innerHTML = '';

      items.forEach((reply: string, index: number) => {
        const card = document.createElement('article');
        card.className = 'output-item relative group';

        const top = document.createElement('div');
        top.className = 'flex items-center justify-between mb-2 pb-2 border-b border-zinc-100';

        const title = document.createElement('strong');
        title.className = 'text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-zinc-400';
        title.textContent = `Option ${index + 1}`;

        const chars = document.createElement('span');
        chars.className = 'text-[11px] font-medium text-zinc-400 bg-zinc-50 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded';
        chars.textContent = `${reply.length} chars`;

        top.append(title, chars);

        const body = document.createElement('p');
        body.className = 'text-[13px] leading-relaxed text-zinc-900 mb-3';
        body.textContent = reply;

        const copyWrap = document.createElement('div');
        
        const copyBtn = document.createElement('button');
        copyBtn.type = 'button';
        copyBtn.className = 'btn btn--secondary btn--sm w-full group-hover:border-zinc-300';
        copyBtn.textContent = 'Copy reply';
        copyBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
          const orig = copyBtn.textContent;
          navigator.clipboard.writeText(reply).then(() => {
            copyBtn.textContent = 'Copied!';
            copyBtn.classList.add('text-emerald-600');
            setTimeout(() => {
              copyBtn.textContent = orig;
              copyBtn.classList.remove('text-emerald-600');
            }, 1500);
          });
        });
        
        copyWrap.append(copyBtn);
        card.append(top, body, copyWrap);
        replyResults.append(card);
      });
    };

    const buildReplies = () => {
      const source = replySource.value.trim();
      const angle = safeText(replyAngle.value || 'a creator workflow angle');

      if (!source) {
        replySource.focus();
        return;
      }

      const topic = summarizeTopic(source);
      const styles: Record<ReplyStyle, string[]> = {
        add_value: [
          `Strong point. One layer I would add for creators is ${angle}. That is usually where the workflow either compounds or breaks.`,
          `This resonates. The missing layer for most people is ${angle}, because that is what turns a good idea into a repeatable posting habit.`,
          `Agreed. I would push one step further: make ${angle} visible in the post itself so readers can apply the idea fast.`,
          `Useful framing. I think ${angle} is the practical bridge between hearing this advice and actually shipping posts with it.`,
        ],
        question: [
          `Curious how you think about ${angle} when the audience is early-stage creators and not full-time operators.`,
          `Good point. What changes in your view when ${topic.toLowerCase()} has to fit a solo-creator workflow with almost no extra time?`,
          `I like this. How would you pressure-test it through the lens of ${angle} instead of pure reach?`,
          `What would you keep manual here if the goal was better thinking, not just more output? That is where ${angle} gets interesting to me.`,
        ],
        agreement: [
          `Yes. The part I would underline is ${angle}. That is usually the difference between content that sounds smart and content that gets used.`,
          `Completely agree. ${angle} is what makes this practical for solo creators who need a workflow, not another theory.`,
          `This is right. I would only add that ${angle} should show up before the CTA, otherwise the post stays abstract.`,
          `Well said. The strongest extension is ${angle}, because that is where readers decide whether the advice is actionable.`,
        ],
        contrarian: [
          `Mostly agree, but I think creators overweight scale and underweight ${angle}. Better drafts usually beat more automation early on.`,
          `I would push back on one piece: ${topic.toLowerCase()} matters less than the consistency of ${angle} when you are still building signal.`,
          `My only disagreement is that this sounds easier to automate than it is. ${angle} still needs human judgment if you want real replies.`,
          `Good take overall. I just think the stronger lever for small creators is ${angle}, not adding more tooling around the edges.`,
        ],
      };

      const style = (replyStyle.value in styles ? replyStyle.value : 'add_value') as ReplyStyle;

      const replies = styles[style].map((reply) => fitPost('', reply).trim());
      renderReplies(replies);
    };

    replyGenerate.addEventListener('click', buildReplies);
  })();
</script>
